    "description": "Nissin Shoji Co.,Ltd. engages in the sale of petroleum products in Japan. The company also offers biomass power generation fuel, such as palm kernel shell and empty fruit bunches pellets; energy saving solutions and marketing; and lubricating and fuel oils; service station services, including car wash and coating, vehicle inspection, repair, and insurance; car sales, leases, and rentals. In addition, it provides functional chemicals, comprising synthetic resin raw, packaging, non-woven, and reflective materials, agricultural covering material, thermal shielding coated sheet for tunnels, thermal insulation material, and reflective materials under the Teru Teru, Warmth, Round Cool, and Warif brand names; photosynthetic efficiency accelerator; CO2 application controller under the OCES-200S and Conductor brand names; agricultural houses, including steel frame, ap, and pipe houses; liquefied petroleum gas, such as propane and industrial gases; and water heaters; built-in hob; industrial boilers; disaster propane gas generator. Further, the company is involved in real estate leasing of office buildings and residences; and new construction and acquisition of properties, and tenant management. Nissin Shoji Co.,Ltd. was incorporated in 1947 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
